
GraphQL tells us you can just Query what you need (n+1) below is the Example, It also works on HTTP, GraphQL only makes POST Call, It works on Single Endpoint "/graphql"


query products {

	id
	title
	thumbnail

}


Now we will only get (ID, TITLE & Thumbnail) in the Response from GraphQL (The Client can Decide what Data they want)





# If we want to Get the Data we will use the Keyword Query (as shown above) with all the required info and its Schema Definition



